725247f-d.text: Thirty-Seventh Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 93rd Street showing the H. S. Leverich house. It was erected in 1840. Fred Schuchardt was the owner in 1891, and Mrs. Viel the occupant in 1922. It was demolished in June 1925. View 3 shows a dilapidated barn in the 93rd Street line. View 4 shows the site upon which the house once stood. August 1923. View 2: 1927. View 3: August 1923. View 4: October 1925. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
